---
import LegalLayout from '../layouts/LegalLayout.astro';
import Prose from '../components/Prose.astro';
import { site } from '../data/site';

const namescape = site.products.find((product) => product.slug === 'namescape')!;
const gateway = site.products.find((product) => product.slug === 'gateway')!;
---
<LegalLayout
  title="Terms of Service"
  description="Terms for Pinkflow, Namescape launch preparation, and the Gateway.pink developer preview."
  lastUpdated={site.lastUpdated.terms}
>
  <Prose>
    <p>These Terms were last updated on {site.lastUpdated.terms}.</p>

    <h2>1. Agreement to these Terms</h2>
    <p>
      By creating an account, using an API key, or using any Pinkflow service, you agree to
      these Terms. If you do not agree, do not use the service.
    </p>

    <h2>2. About Pinkflow and these services</h2>
    <p>
      {site.operatorLine}. These Terms currently cover {namescape.name}
      and {gateway.name}, as well as company pages at pinkflow.ai.
    </p>
    <p>
      Namescape is in launch preparation. The implemented Gateway.pink catalog is a developer
      preview, but public API and documentation access are not currently open. Neither product
      is a currently open public purchase offer.
    </p>

    <h2>3. What Namescape does</h2>
    <p>
      Namescape takes a description of an idea and produces domain-name suggestions with
      price guidance, likely-availability clues, and final checks. Suggestions
      help you shortlist names; they do not guarantee availability, price, or legal clearance.
    </p>

    <h2>4. What Gateway.pink does</h2>
    <p>
      The implemented Gateway.pink developer-preview catalog defines utility, public-data,
      validation, rendering, lookup, and model-backed APIs intended to work behind one key.
      Public API and documentation access are not currently open. If invitation-preview access
      is offered, each shared route contract will identify its price, data source, and storage policy.
    </p>

    <h2>5. Accounts and API keys</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>You must be at least 16 years old to create an account or hold a production API key.</li>
      <li>Provide accurate information and keep it current.</li>
      <li>You are responsible for your account sessions, credentials, and API keys.</li>
      <li>Do not share a personal account or publish a secret API key.</li>
      <li>Contact us promptly if you believe a credential has been compromised.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>6. Namescape searches and Gateway credits</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Namescape launch pricing uses one-time search packs in USD. See <a href="/pricing#namescape">Namescape pricing</a>.</li>
      <li>A paid Namescape action deducts its published search amount only after the paid work returns a usable result.</li>
      <li>At launch, signed-out trial attempts will be rate-limited and will not be a paid balance.</li>
      <li>Gateway.pink defines one credit as $0.001. Fixed routes have a published per-call price; metered AI calls settle from provider-reported cost subject to the caller's budget, and browser preview routes settle from provider-reported browser time.</li>
      <li>Paid Gateway requests require a valid, unique <code>Idempotency-Key</code>. Reusing a key does not repeat the provider call or debit.</li>
      <li>Gateway.pink credit checkout is not currently available. Published packs are preview prices, not purchasable offers today.</li>
      <li>Balances are non-transferable, have no cash value, and cannot be resold.</li>
      <li>Neither product has a subscription or auto-renewal.</li>
      <li>Purchases are generally final once delivered or used. See the <a href="/refunds">Refund Policy</a>.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>7. Payments</h2>
    <p>
      Eligible purchases are processed by Paddle, the {site.paddle.role.toLowerCase()}.
      Your card statement will show <strong>{site.paddle.statementLabel}</strong>. Paddle may
      calculate tax and display a localized total before checkout. We do not receive your full
      card number.
    </p>

    <h2>8. Responsible use</h2>
    <p>You will not:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Use a service for unlawful activity, trademark infringement, cybersquatting, abuse, or attacks.</li>
      <li>Bypass rate limits, billing controls, authentication, or published usage limits.</li>
      <li>Scrape, bulk-harvest, or resell outputs or service access contrary to the product contract.</li>
      <li>Use Gateway.pink to target private networks, exfiltrate secrets, distribute malware, or interfere with another system.</li>
      <li>Misrepresent Pinkflow output as a guarantee or professional legal, financial, or security advice.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>9. Your inputs and provider processing</h2>
    <p>
      You retain your rights in the inputs you submit. You grant Pinkflow the limited right to
      process them to provide, secure, and support the requested service. A provider-backed
      feature may transmit the input required for that call to the named upstream provider;
      the product terms or route contract shared for that access and our
      <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a> explain those boundaries.
    </p>
    <p>Do not submit data you are not authorized to process or disclose.</p>

    <h2>10. Outputs and third-party information</h2>
    <p>
      Generated names, availability signals, public records, provider validations, screenshots,
      model output, and other results can be incomplete, delayed, or incorrect. Verify important
      information with the relevant registrar, registry, provider, authority, or source before
      relying on it.
    </p>

    <h2>11. Service changes and availability</h2>
    <p>
      We do not guarantee uninterrupted access. Preview routes, sources, models, prices, and
      features may change or be withdrawn. We may restrict access for maintenance, security,
      abuse, legal requirements, or violations of these Terms.
    </p>

    <h2>12. Intellectual property</h2>
    <p>
      Pinkflow owns its brands, site content, and proprietary service components. Open-source
      components and public standards remain subject to their own licenses. These Terms do not
      override rights granted by an applicable open-source license.
    </p>

    <h2>13. Disclaimers</h2>
    <p>
      Services are provided "as is" and "as available." To the maximum extent permitted by
      law, we disclaim implied warranties of merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose,
      non-infringement, and uninterrupted or error-free operation.
    </p>

    <h2>14. Limitation of liability</h2>
    <p>
      To the maximum extent permitted by law, Pinkflow and its operator are not liable for
      indirect, incidental, special, or consequential damages arising from a service. Our total
      aggregate liability for a claim is limited to the amount you paid Pinkflow in the 12 months
      before the claim. This does not limit non-waivable consumer rights or liability that cannot
      legally be excluded.
    </p>

    <h2>15. Suspension and termination</h2>
    <p>
      You may stop using a service or request account deletion. We may suspend or terminate
      access for material violations, abuse, security risk, non-payment, or legal requirements,
      with notice where reasonable.
    </p>

    <h2>16. Changes and governing law</h2>
    <p>
      We may update these Terms and will revise the date above. For material changes, we will
      provide reasonable notice through the relevant service or account email. These Terms are
      governed by the laws of {site.jurisdiction}, without regard to conflict-of-law principles.
    </p>

    <h2>17. Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Questions about these Terms? Email <a href={`mailto:${site.email}`}>{site.email}</a> or use
      the <a href="/contact">contact page</a>.
    </p>
  </Prose>
</LegalLayout>
